This paper is primarily focused on intrusion detection and anonymity, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also deals with traffic analysis and detection, which is a subfield of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of hypothesis testing and simulation techniques suggests that this paper may also belong to the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of optimum detectors, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
